                <head>200. Summary of Conclusions of a Special Coordination Committee Meeting<note
                        n="1" type="source" xml:id="d200fn1">Source: Carter Library, National
                        Security Council, <gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss> Institutional Files
                        (H–Files), Box 110. Top Secret. The meeting took place in the White House
                        Situation Room. <persName corresp="#p_CJ_1">Carter</persName> wrote “Zbig,
                        C” in the upper right corner. Beginning February 9, the 9 a.m. <gloss
                            target="#t_SCC_1">SCC</gloss> meetings on Iran met only on Tuesdays and
                        Thursdays. (Memorandum from <persName corresp="#p_BZ_1"
                            >Brzezinski</persName> to <persName corresp="#p_VC_1">Vance</persName>,
                            <persName corresp="#p_BH_1">Brown</persName>, <persName
                            corresp="#p_JDC_1">Jones</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_TS_2"
                            >Turner</persName>, February 8; Carter Library, National Security
                        Affairs, Staff Material, Office File, Box 18, <gloss target="#t_SCC_1"
                            >SCC</gloss> Meeting #264 held 1/30/80)</note>
                </head>
